claim: Dominican Republic is the second-largest Caribbean nation by population.
premise_source_doc_sentence: The Dominican Republic is the second-largest Caribbean nation by area  (  after Cuba  )  at 48445 km2 , and 3rd by population with approximately 10 million people , of which approximately three million live in the metropolitan area of Santo Domingo , the capital city .
